The paper deals with communication networks and multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses practical capacity-achieving schemes and joint source-channel problems, which fall under the signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new approach called "network modulation," which could potentially be of interest to researchers studying MIMO systems (cs.MM).
